<subSubSection id="DF9FD4D1FDC04074A7AD7828EA746F0B" pageId="1" pageNumber="78" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="5AC8EFA67DB4E4DB138B86F762B049FF" pageId="1" pageNumber="78">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F225D6F036E98B367FBC06F1F2E88751" pageId="1" pageNumber="78">
<taxonomicName id="15C4E54B075E85B01C7ABD85BB78BF2A" authorityName="Z. W. Wang &amp; H. C. Xi" authorityYear="2019" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Berberidaceae" genus="Dysosma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Dysosma villosa" order="Ranunculales" pageId="1" pageNumber="78" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="villosa">
<emphasis id="E9C63E99722DA54842DF0ADCAB7A7EC0" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="78">Dysosma villosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="483176494910F4568E2B9999C9A67E34" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Berberidaceae" genus="D." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="D. difformis" order="Ranunculales" pageId="1" pageNumber="78" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="difformis">
<emphasis id="B8863270B45569C786E06BBC901B1AB3" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="78">D. difformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Hemsl. &amp; E.H.Wilson) T.H.Wang 
<emphasis id="265ED167805BEC9B7A7E3A070D3A66D1" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="78">ex</emphasis>
T.S.Ying, but differs from the latter by its inflorescences generally with more flowers (5-13 vs. 2-5), white-villous petioles, stems and abaxial leaf blade and dark purple-red stigma.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
